?? E-Commerce API (Project Phase 1 – Setup & EF Core)
------------------------------------------------------

?? Mission 1 – Create the Project

?? Open Visual Studio Community 
?? Create ASP.NET Core Web API project
?? Name: ECommerceAPI
?? Target Framework: .NET 8.0
? Authentication: None
? Enable Use Controllers

? Goal: Clean Web API base project ready for configuration.

?? Mission 2 – Install Required NuGet Packages

?? Open Tools ? NuGet Package Manager ? Package Manager Console
?? Run the following:

Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore -Version 8.0.0
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer -Version 8.0.0
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools -Version 8.0.0
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design -Version 8.0.0


? Goal: EF Core fully integrated with SQL Server provider and migration tools.

?? Mission 3 – Create Project Folders

?? Add folders under the root project:

?? Models
?? Data
?? DTOs
?? Controllers


? Goal: Clean, scalable architecture for future features.

?? Mission 4 – Prepare Database Connection

? Open appsettings.json
? Add the connection string placeholder:

"ConnectionStrings": {
  "DefaultConnection": "Server=.;Database=ECommerceDb;Trusted_Connection=True;TrustServerCertificate=True;"
}


? Goal: Ready for EF Core context and DB connection.

?? Mission 5 – Run & Verify

? Press Ctrl + F5 to run the project
? Confirm Swagger UI opens at
https://localhost:xxxx/swagger

? Goal: Project builds and runs successfully.

?? Phase 1 Status:

? Mission 1  ? Mission 2  ? Mission 3  ? Mission 4  ? Mission 5





